{{rank|met|boy|c.|397|strong|dead|bring|returned}}

===Etymology===
From Middle English, from Old English [[strang]].
===Pronunciation===
*strŏng, /strɒŋ/, /strQN/

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-er}}

#Capable of [[produce|producing]] great physical [[force]]. (''a strong man'')
#Capable of [[withstand]]ing great physical force. (''a strong foundation'')
#[[Determined]], [[unyielding]]. (''He is strong in the face of adversity.'')
#Highly [[stimulate|stimulating]] to the [[sense]]s. (''strong light'', ''a strong taste'')
#[[Concentrate]]d. (''strong coffee'')
#(''Grammar'') [[Irregular]]. (''strong verb'')
#(''Colloquial, slang:  US'') Impressive, good (''You're working with troubled youth in your off time? That's strong'')

